Anymouse <honeybus(-at-)gmail.com> wrote:
>Once Blake removes those hoses to the engine compartment, what does he
>do with the two holes that will be left??  I mean, they have to be
>'solved' or Blake won't have a sealed engine compartment.
>
>And what is the diameter of those holes, so what kind of plug or
> grommet could fit those holes.

Tack weld a patch of sheet metal over the hole in the left
rear wheel well.  This keeps the dirt, road salt and hot air
from entering the engine room.  Worked for me.

>
>Suggestions sought, and neatness counts...

Grind down the welds, paint & undercoat for a pretty wheel well.

